{
  "message": "\ud83c\udfa8 fix: align News and Reviews icons with Community dropdown style (#1483) (#1484)\n\nThe Community dropdown uses a consistent stroke-based outline icon\nstyle (fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" with\nstrokeLinecap/strokeLinejoin=\"round\" strokeWidth=\"2\") for every item\nexcept News and Reviews:\n\n- News was a filled custom SVG path (megaphone-style) with no stroke\n  attributes and a different path semantic from the other icons.\n- Reviews was a Unicode emoji (&#127917; clapperboard) with a\n  trailing &nbsp;, rendering as an OS-dependent glyph that clashed\n  visually with the outline SVGs.\n\nReplaces News with a newspaper outline icon and Reviews with a star\noutline icon, both sharing the same size, stroke, and viewBox as the\nrest of the dropdown items.\n\nFixes #1483\n\nSigned-off-by: Andy Anderson <andy@clubanderson.com>",
